  "prompt": "How many offices does Google have around the world?  Which countries are they in?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, Google operates **over 70 offices** in **more than 50 countries** around the world. These offices are strategically located to support Google's global operations, including engineering, sales, marketing, and other functions. Here's an overview of some of the key countries and regions where Google has established a significant presence:\n\n### **North America**\n- **United States:** Multiple locations including Mountain View (headquarters), New York City, Seattle, Chicago, Austin, and more.\n- **Canada:** Cities like Toronto, Vancouver, and Montreal.\n\n### **Europe**\n- **United Kingdom:** London (largest European hub).\n- **Germany:** Berlin, Munich, Hamburg.\n- **France:** Paris.\n- **Ireland:** Dublin (European headquarters).\n- **Netherlands:** Amsterdam.\n- **Sweden, Switzerland, Spain, Italy, and others.**\n\n### **Asia-Pacific**\n- **India:** Multiple offices including Bangalore, Mumbai, and Hyderabad.\n- **Japan:** Tokyo.\n- **China:** While Google\u2019s services are limited in mainland China, it maintains offices in areas like Hong Kong.\n- **Singapore, Australia (Sydney, Melbourne), South Korea, Taiwan, and others.**\n\n### **Latin America**\n- **Brazil:** S\u00e3o Paulo, Rio de Janeiro.\n- **Mexico:** Mexico City.\n- **Argentina, Chile, Colombia, and others.**\n\n### **Middle East and Africa**\n- **Israel, United Arab Emirates (Dubai), South Africa (Johannesburg, Cape Town), Nigeria, and others.**\n\n### **Other Regions**\n- Google also has offices in countries like Russia, Poland, Czech Republic, Belgium, and more, serving various regional markets.\n\n### **Key Points:**\n- **Diversity of Locations:** Google\u2019s offices range from major metropolitan areas to specialized tech hubs, facilitating access to diverse talent pools and regional markets.\n- **Global Functions:** Different offices may focus on specific functions such as software development, sales, marketing, customer support, research, and development.\n- **Expansion and Changes:** Google continues to expand its global footprint, and the number of offices can change based on strategic needs, market conditions, and other factors.\n\nFor the most up-to-date and detailed information, it's recommended to visit [Google's official careers or company locations page](https://www.google.com/about/locations/) or consult recent corporate reports.",
